      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead lead-big">Vacancies – How to Apply</span></p>
<p>Thank you for considering an application to work for Queen Margaret University. We pride ourselves on our excellent procedures for the recruitment and selection of our staff. We encourage applications from applicants of all backgrounds. Our processes are designed to ensure that the best candidate is selected for every role based on their skills, abilities and experience.</p>
<p>The recruitment process is managed by the QMU HR team, if you have any questions about the recruitment and selection process please email <a href="mailto:recruitment@qmu.ac.uk">recruitment@qmu.ac.uk</a> or contact the HR team on (0131) 474 0000.</p>
<p>Please see our <a href="/footer/vacancies/qmu-recruitment-privacy-notice/" title="QMU Recruitment Privacy Notice">QMU Recruitment Privacy Notice </a>and <a href="/footer/foi-and-data-protection/data-protection-policy/" title="Data Protection Policy">Data Protection Policy.</a></p>
<p>See the relevant web sections for more information on other <a data-id="6221" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4244556999c841fdacc0f5eb17272d83}" title="Privacy Statement">privacy statements</a> and <a data-id="4583" href="/{localLink:umb://document/5adad35d05b1490597fc18a3622e0072}" title="FOI and Data Protection">data protection</a>.</p>
<p><span class="lead">Applying Online</span></p>
<p>Queen Margaret University has an online recruitment system and all applicants should submit an online application form. To view our current vacancies please click on the link below.</p>
<p><a rel="noopener" href="https://ce0011li.webitrent.com/ce0011li_webrecruitment/wrd/run/ETREC105GF.open?WVID=6368270VSq" target="_blank" title="QMU Vacancies- Recruitment System" data-anchor="?WVID=6368270VSq"><span class="blue-btn">View Current Vacancies</span></a> <strong>(Opens in a new window)</strong></p>
<p>Once you have selected the vacancy you wish to apply for click ‘Apply’, you can then set up an account or login (if you already have an account set up).</p>
<p>The guidance notes for applicants also available below will guide applicants through the process of setting up an account on our online system and completing the application form.</p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><a rel="noopener" href="/footer/vacancies/queen-margaret-university-job-applicant-guidance-notes/" target="_blank" title="Job Applicant Guidance Notes">Job Applicant Guidance Notes</a> (Opens in a new window)</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><span class="lead">Applicants with a Disability </span></p>
<p>Queen Margaret University offers an interview to applicants with a disability so long as they satisfy the essential criteria for the post as set out within the person specification. You must declare your disability on the online application form and provide details of any adjustments you would require for interview. We understand that it will not be possible for some applicants with a disability to complete the the online application form, if this is the case for you the application for is available in alternative formats, please contact the HR team on the contact details outlined above.</p>
<p><span class="lead">Eligibility to Work in the UK </span></p>
<p>In order for the university to confirm that job applicants are eligible to work in the UK if you are invited to interview you will be asked to provide eligibility of your right to work in the UK, usually this is in the form of a passport however there other options which the HR team will advise you of when if are invited to interview. Please note that original copies of your ID must be seen, photocopies will not be accepted.</p>
<p><span class="lead">Applicants from outwith the European Economic Area (EEA) </span></p>
<p>Queen Margaret University accepts and considers applications from those outwith the EEA. We are able to offer sponsorship for skilled workers under the Tier 2 points based system.</p>
<p>For Queen Margaret University to issue you with a Tier 2 Certificate of Sponsorship a number of conditions must be met including criteria for the advertisement of the vacancy, skill and salary level of the position. With this in mind not every position the university recruits for will be eligible for sponsorship under Tier 2, normally job adverts will indicate whether Tier 2 sponsorship is a possibility. Further information regarding sponsorship under Tier 2 can be found at the following link <a href="https://www.gov.uk/tier-2-general/overview" title="Tier 2 Sponsorship Information">gov.uk/tier-2-general/overview</a></p>
<p><span class="lead">Next Steps </span></p>
<p>Once you have submitted your application form and following the application closing date your application will be sent to the shortlisting panel for consideration. Once shortlisting has taken place you will receive an email from us either inviting you to book an interview slot on a specific date or declining your application. We regret that due to the high volume of applications we receive it is not possible for us to provide feedback on your application if you are unsuccessful in being invited to interview.</p>
<p> </p>]]></Value>
